{{Quote|At first, Bail would not hear of it. He was aghast at the very idea of attempting to overthrow the government he had given his whole life to. For a moment after I broached the subject, I thought he was going to have me arrested. It wasn't until the Ghorman Massacre that he turned around. After Ghorman, Bail realized that the Republic was dead. He began to use all of his influence and political skill to aid us, while still pretending to be against me on the floor of the Senate.|Mon Mothma|<ref name="TRAS" />}}
The '''Cantham House Meetings''', also known as '''the Cantham talks''', were a series of meetings between [[Senator/Legends|Senators]] [[Bail Prestor Organa/Legends|Bail Organa]], [[Mon Mothma/Legends|Mon Mothma]], and occasionally [[Garm Bel Iblis/Legends|Garm Bel Iblis]] at [[Cantham House/Legends|Cantham House]] on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]]. The subject of these meetings was usually the formation of an [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|organized resistance]] against [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine's]] [[New Order/Legends|New Order]].

